Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1}(drained and rinsed) in a #colander.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{for the salsa}(a drizzle) in a #frying pan{} on high heat. When the oil is hot, add the @British beef mince{120%g} and cook until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #wooden spoon{} to break it up as it cooks. Drain and discard any excess fat from the beef, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the onion and cook until the onion is soft, ~{4-5%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Add the garlic and @chipotle paste{20%g} (use less chipotle paste if you don't like heat), stir and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Pour in the @water{300%ml}, stir in the @vegetable stock powder{1}, @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g} and add the @red split lentils{100%g}. Stir together, bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to medium, cover with a #lid{} and simmer until the lentils are tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Stir every few minutes to ensure the lentils aren't sticking to the bottom of the pan. Add the kidney beans for the final 5 mins, and a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

> MOD Step: Before you cook the onion in the step above, heat a drizzle of oil in a frying pan on high heat. When the oil is hot, add the beef mince and cook until browned, 5-6 mins. Use a wooden spoon to break it up as it cooks. Drain and discard any excess fat from the beef, then season with salt and pepper. Add the onion and continue with the step and the recipe as instructed.

Pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. When the water is boiling, add 1/4 tsp of @salt{}, stir in the @basmati rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a lid on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While the rice and chilli cooks, grate the @lime{1}(grated zest) and halve the lime. Quarter the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}(quartered) and finely chop the @coriander{1}(finely chopped) (stalks and all). Squeeze half the lime juice into a #bowl{} and add the @olive oil{for the salsa}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir together, then add the tomatoes and coriander. Mix together and keep to one side.

Once cooked, fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir in the lime zest. Spoon into #bowls{}, top with the beef and lentil chilli and finish with the tomato and coriander salsa and a dollop of @soured cream{75%g}. Cut the remaining lime into wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!